{% extends '_layout' %}

{% block content %}
    
    <div class="hero hero-bluebg pt-32 md:pt-40 pb-32 md:pb-48">
        <div class="center-content">
            <div class="max-w-xl m-auto text-white text-center px-4">
                <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-5xl leading-tight mb-6 md:mb-10 font-heading">Contact <span style="color: {{ entry.pageTheme.value }};">Servd Demo</span></h2>
                <p class="text-lg md:text-2xl mb-8 md:mb-12 font-light leading-tight">Absolutely Fantastic!</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="-mt-12 md:-mt-24 pb-12 md:pb-24">
        <div class="center-content">
            
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-light py-12 md:py-16 text-blue-dark">
        <div class="center-content center-content-slim">
            <h3 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-center sm:text-left font-heading mb-8">
                Optimised Images
            </h3>
            <p class="mb-4">
                When you use Servd's helper plugin and asset platform for storing your images, they'll
                automatically be transformed and optimised off-server, and distributed to end users via a global 
                CDN.
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="py-12 text-blue-dark">
        <div class="center-content center-content-slim">
            <h3 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-center sm:text-left font-heading mb-8">
                Static Caching
            </h3>
            <p class="mb-4">
                Activate static caching and snapshots of your project's responses will be stored
                and delivered to end users. You can even add simple path prefixes for content which 
                should never be cached.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-4">
                Users logged into the Craft Control Panel will always skip the cache. So you don't have 
                to worry about admin-only content getting added to the cache.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-4">
                The Servd Helper plugin will automatically clear the cache whenever changes are made in 
                Craft Control Panel. You can also force clear the cache at any time.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-light py-12 md:py-16 text-blue-dark">
        <div class="center-content center-content-slim">
            <h3 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-center sm:text-left font-heading mb-8">
                Backup &amp; Restore
            </h3>
            <p class="mb-4">
                Servd will take regular backups of your project. These backups include:
            </p>
            <ul class="mb-4 pl-4">
                <li>- The database</li>
                <li>- Assets stored on the Servd Asset Platform</li>
                <li>- The currently deployed commit</li>
                <li>- The current PHP version</li>
                <li>- Your project's settings in the Servd Dashboard</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mb-4">
                You can restore a backup with a single click. It usually takes less between 30 seconds and 2 minutes to complete the entire restore process!
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="py-12 md:py-16 text-blue-dark">
        <div class="center-content center-content-slim">
            <h3 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-center sm:text-left font-heading mb-8">
                Staging Environment
            </h3>
            <p class="mb-4">
                Every project has a Staging environment which you can use to test updates and migrations.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-4">
                Cloning data and assets between your environments is just a single click process in the Servd Dashboard and only takes seconds.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

{% endblock %}
